// ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ BEACON MODE SCREEN ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
// Layout (128√ó64):
//  [00-10] Status bar:  ‚Ėļ BEACON  |  BOOT#N
//  [13-28] Frequency large (2√ó)
//  [30-36] TX progress bar (full width, rounded)
//  [38-44] Message text + WPM badge
//  [46-53] "TRANSMITTING" blink OR sleep countdown
//  [55-63] Freq index indicator dots
void oledBeacon(int freqIdx, float freqMHz, int charIdx, int totalChars,
                uint32_t cycleNum, uint32_t sleepRemainSec, bool transmitting) {
  if (!g_oledOk || !cfg.oledEnabled) return;
  if (millis() - g_lastOledUpdate < OLED_REFRESH_MS && !transmitting) return;
  g_lastOledUpdate = millis();

  oled.clearDisplay();

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Status bar ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  char rightBuf[14];
  snprintf(rightBuf, sizeof(rightBuf), "BOOT#%lu", cycleNum);
  oledStatusBar("> BEACON", rightBuf);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Frequency (large) ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setTextSize(2);
  oled.setCursor(0, 14);
  char fbuf[12];
  snprintf(fbuf, sizeof(fbuf), "%.3f", freqMHz);
  oled.print(fbuf);
  oled.setTextSize(1);
  oled.setCursor(104, 21);
  oled.print("MHz");

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ TX progress bar ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  uint8_t pct = (totalChars > 0) ? (uint8_t)(charIdx * 100 / totalChars) : 0;
  oledBar(0, 31, 128, 7, pct);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Message + WPM ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setTextSize(1);
  oled.setCursor(0, 41);
  char msgBuf[18];
  snprintf(msgBuf, sizeof(msgBuf), "%-17s", cfg.message);
  oled.print(msgBuf);
  // WPM badge (right aligned)
  char wpmBuf[7];
  snprintf(wpmBuf, sizeof(wpmBuf), "%dWPM", cfg.wpm);
  oled.setCursor(128 - strlen(wpmBuf)*6 - 1, 41);
  oled.print(wpmBuf);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Status row ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  if (transmitting) {
    if ((millis() / 350) % 2 == 0) {
      oled.fillRoundRect(14, 51, 100, 10, 3, SH110X_WHITE);
      oled.setTextColor(SH110X_BLACK);
      oled.setCursor(21, 53);
      oled.print("* TRANSMITTING *");
      oled.setTextColor(SH110X_WHITE);
    }
  } else {
    oled.setCursor(0, 53);
    oled.print("SLEEP ");
    oled.print(sleepRemainSec);
    oled.print("s");
  }

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Freq index dots ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  for (int i = 0; i < (int)cfg.freqCount && i < 10; i++) {
    int16_t dx = 128 - cfg.freqCount * 7 + i * 7;
    if (i == freqIdx)
      oled.fillCircle(dx, 59, 3, SH110X_WHITE);
    else
      oled.drawCircle(dx, 59, 2, SH110X_WHITE);
  }

  oled.display();
}

// ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ SEARCH MODE SCREEN ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
// Layout:
//  [00-10] Status bar: ‚óą SEARCH | HITS:N
//  [13-28] Current frequency (large)
//  [30-37] RSSI value + signal bar (graphical)
//  [39-48] Signal label (STRONG/MEDIUM/WEAK/SCANNING) ‚ÄĒ big + highlighted
//  [50-57] Pass# | Channel | Threshold
//  [58-63] Audio tone indicator
void oledSearch(int freqIdx, float freqMHz, int16_t rssi,
                uint32_t passNum, bool detected) {
  if (!g_oledOk || !cfg.oledEnabled) return;
  if (millis() - g_lastOledUpdate < OLED_REFRESH_MS) return;
  g_lastOledUpdate = millis();

  oled.clearDisplay();

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Status bar ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  char hitsBuf[10];
  snprintf(hitsBuf, sizeof(hitsBuf), "HIT:%d", g_scanHitCount);
  oledStatusBar("* SEARCH", hitsBuf);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Frequency ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setTextSize(2);
  oled.setCursor(0, 14);
  char fbuf[12];
  snprintf(fbuf, sizeof(fbuf), "%.3f", freqMHz);
  oled.print(fbuf);
  oled.setTextSize(1);
  oled.setCursor(104, 21);
  oled.print("MHz");

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ RSSI value + bar ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setTextSize(1);
  oled.setCursor(0, 31);
  char rbuf[12];
  snprintf(rbuf, sizeof(rbuf), "%4ddBm", rssi);
  oled.print(rbuf);

  // Signal bar (76 wide)
  uint8_t rssiPct = rssiToPct(rssi);
  oledBar(44, 30, 84, 7, rssiPct);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Signal label (highlighted when detected) ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  if (detected && (millis() / 300) % 2 == 0) {
    const char* lbl;
    if      (rssi >= -60) lbl = "!!! STRONG !!!";
    else if (rssi >= -80) lbl = "!!  MEDIUM  !!";
    else                  lbl = "!   WEAK    !";
    oled.fillRoundRect(0, 39, 128, 12, 3, SH110X_WHITE);
    oled.setTextColor(SH110X_BLACK);
    oled.setCursor(4, 42);
    oled.print(lbl);
    oled.setTextColor(SH110X_WHITE);
  } else if (g_scanHitCount > 0) {
    // Show last hit
    oled.setCursor(0, 41);
    oled.print("LAST:");
    snprintf(fbuf, sizeof(fbuf), "%.3f", g_scanHits[g_scanHitCount-1].freq);
    oled.print(fbuf);
    oled.print("MHz ");
    oled.print(g_scanHits[g_scanHitCount-1].rssi);
    oled.print("dBm");
  } else {
    oled.setCursor(0, 41);
    oled.print("SCANNING...");
  }

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Signal bars (graphical) ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oledSignalBars(93, 64, rssiToBars(rssi));

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Pass + channel ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setCursor(0, 53);
  oled.print("PASS#");
  oled.print(passNum);
  oled.print("  CH:");
  oled.print(freqIdx + 1);
  oled.print("/");
  oled.print(cfg.freqCount);

  // ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ Audio status ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
  oled.setCursor(0, 61);
  if (cfg.audioEnabled) {
    uint32_t toneFreq = audioSearchTone(rssi);
    if (toneFreq > 0) {
      oled.print("\x0E ");
      oled.print(toneFreq);
      oled.print("Hz");
    } else {
      oled.print("AUDIO:SILENT");
    }
  } else {
    oled.print("AUDIO:OFF");
  }
  oled.print(" T:");
  oled.print(cfg.rssiThreshold);

  oled.display();
}

// ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ EMERGENCY SCREEN ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ
void oledEmergency(float freqMHz, uint32_t cycleNum) {
  if (!g_oledOk || !cfg.oledEnabled) return;
  if (millis() - g_lastOledUpdate < 150) return;
  g_lastOledUpdate = millis();

  oled.clearDisplay();

  bool inv = (millis() / 400) % 2;
  if (inv) {
    oled.fillScreen(SH110X_WHITE);
    oled.setTextColor(SH110X_BLACK);
  } else {
    oled.setTextColor(SH110X_WHITE);
  }

  // Giant SOS ‚ÄĒ textSize 3 = 18px tall, 3 chars = 54px wide
  oled.setTextSize(3);
  oled.setCursor(19, 4);
  oled.print("SOS");

  // Border accent lines
  oled.drawFastHLine(0, 27, 128, inv ? SH110X_BLACK : SH110X_WHITE);

  oled.setTextSize(1);
  oled.setCursor(4, 31);
  oled.print("!! EMERGENCY MODE !!");

  oled.setCursor(4, 43);
  char fbuf[24];
  snprintf(fbuf, sizeof(fbuf), "TX %.3f MHz", freqMHz);
  oled.print(fbuf);

  oled.setCursor(4, 55);
  oled.print("CYCLE #");
  oled.print(cycleNum);

  oled.display();
}

